 Kwara State House of Assembly  The bill is an executive bill forwarded to the House by Gov. AbdulRahman AbdulRasaq during Tuesdayâ€™s plenary of the House. The motion for the presentation of a report on the bill and the second reading of the bill which was moved by the House leader, Abubakar Olawoyin-Magaji, enjoyed the support of all members at plenary. The bill passed the second reading after an intensive debate on it by some members. Leading the debate on the bill, the House leader said the law enacted in Dec, 2010
made provision for payment of pension to former Governors and Deputy Governors as specified by Revenue Mobilisation Allocation and Fiscal Commission. He noted that under the law, former Governors and Deputy Governors were provided with accommodation, transport, domestic staff, security, entertainment, among others. The House leader described the repeal of the law as the best thing to happen to the state. Other lawmakers who contributed during the debate on the bill spoke in similar vein and called for urgent passage of the bill. The Speaker, Mr Yakubu Danladi, forwarded the bill to the House Committee on Establishment and Training to work on it and report back to House in due course.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .